The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                     London: Prakash Amritraj sealed a second round berth in the Wimbledon qualifying event but it was all over for Somdev Dev Varman, who crashed out after losing his opening match here on Monday. Prakash, seeded 28th and ranked 161 beat Croatian world No. 236 Antonio Veic 6-3 6-4 in his first round match. Somdev, seeded 14th, lost 3-6, 2-6 to Monaco rsquo;s Jean-Rene Lisnard, who is placed 80 rungs below the Indian at 215.
        Singapore: India continued their goal-scoring spree and thrashed Belgium 4-0 in their second group G match for ninth to 16th position playoff in the FIH Junior Men rsquo;s Hockey World Cup here on Monday. Captain Diwakar Ram, Mohammad Amir Khan, Victo Singh and Jay Karan scored a goal each to ensure the facile win for India at the Seng Kang Sports Complex
            Milan: Italian champions Inter Milan are hopeful of soon signing Chelsea duo Deco and Ricardo Carvalho, club president Massimo Moratti said on Monday. Midfielder Deco played for Inter coach Jose Mourinho at Porto where they won the 2004 Champions League while centre back Carvalho won two Premier League titles under his Portuguese compatriot at Chelsea.
            Calcutta: Mohun Bagan will issue a letter to the All India Football Federation to clarify their stand on the release of players for national duty. ldquo;We rsquo;ve never said of disallowing players for national duty. We rsquo;ll release footballers only in accordance with the Fifa and AFC rule, rdquo; Bagan general secreatry Anjan Mitra said on Monday.          Calcutta: Mohammedan Sporting along with Mumbai club Mahindra United will take part in a four-nation tournament in South Africa to be held in Durban from July 18-26. The tournament is being organised by the Indian Settlement Community to commemorate their 150th anniversary.          Panaji: Goa chief minister Digambar Kamat has announced Rs one lakh to each member of the state team that won the Santosh Trophy in Chennai defeating Bengal via tie-breaker on Sunday. 
                New Delhi: Promising youngster Sourav Saha has been included in a 12-member junior Indian squad for the US Open Table Tennis Championships to be held from July 1-4 in Las Vegas.
